	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I guess this spells liking is up to the individual.  Though it doesn't always work, but when this spell does it is highly effective.  I have taken some chances with this spell and fought creatures that con yellow and red to me and won without takening to much damage.  <BR>
I use the following method of attack when root works.  <BR>
1.  Cast root<BR>
2.  Shoot arrow while recovering<BR>
3.  Burst of Fire<BR>
4.  Repeat steps 2 &amp; 3<BR>
<BR>
I have found that more than 60% of the time.  I run out of mana before the root wears off.  By this time.  Creature is normally half its hp's.  Now I am ready to stand in and melee.  Be forwarned though, this spell doesn't always work, but is very useful.  Another great use for this spell is if you are being attacked by more than one thing.  If you can get the spell off, root one of the others and back away so you have less hitting you at once.  This has saved me more times than not.  <BR>
<BR>
Sinjon<BR>
Prexus
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
