	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Another great use for this spell: Taunt<BR>
<BR>
As a level 15 Ranger, I hunt almost exclusively with my companion, a level 15 druid.  She usually will cast stinging swarm on the harder mobs, and melee / nuke while the swarm is working its damage.  Usually, this will aggro the mob onto her, and although my taunt is capped at my level it is hard to pull it back off her.<BR>
<BR>
This is where a root spell shines, cast it on the mob and watch them go aggro on you.  Even if it fails to aggro the mob on you, your now mauled party member (usually nuker) can safely back up from the fight.<BR>
<BR>
If used correctly this spell is a life saver.  Although I prefer snare for mob movement control, this root spell serves a very nice purpose.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
